Feeding an obese child: Don’t take breakfast and take food for dinner
More than one-third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren are over-average and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families that have an unhealthy lifestyle.
This once again shows how important the environment in which the human being evolves and the patterns that surround him are.
On the tables of obese children, for example, charcoal is found 50% more often than in families of children with a normal weight.
19% of obese people had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an action of awareness "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the big little sports is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% responded that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
A survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 students from Czech primary schools.
This was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", an action supported by the General Health Insurance and the company Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third grade have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children who are overweight, or even obese, is the lack of proper nutrition and insufficient exercise.
"Only half of the children surveyed indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case-lunch-tasting-dinner, which is one of the basic principles of good nutrition," one of the findings of the survey says.
No breakfast and snacks at dinner.
Experts draw attention to the fact that in order to have a healthy development you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of school families eat at the same time.
Most families eat breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that has been noted is that one-tenth of the population doesn’t eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of good daily nutrition.
The questionnaire showed that in families of obese children, unhealthy fries are consumed more often.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sweetened drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children surveyed do sports regularly, but for parents this is half, only 15%.
Prepare your food.
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own meals from options offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
“The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from the ideal in terms of healthy eating.”
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming is, in particular, a high preference for sweetened limonades," the survey finds.
For lunch, it was the pasta that took the first place just ahead of the white meat.
The children did not want fertilizers at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Head to Health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive ad hoc information.
“During a control of a group of survey participants who had filled out the questionnaire after the ‘Obesity is not a coincidence’ awareness session, a determined willingness to move towards a healthy diet was demonstrated,” the survey finds.
The most striking was, for example, when it comes to sweetened limonades as children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often checked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as the main dish and would reduce sweetened dishes and the "knedliky" (Czech specialty of bread flour or potato chips).
