The Need for Speed Run is disputed all over America.
Revision of
Originally a trouble-free race turns into a set of stupid mistakes by people who have nothing to do with a routine morning trip to work.
It fulfills everyone’s ambition to a certain extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do anything else.
The new subtitled The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already outdated Need for Speed racing series and bring out a kind of game from the playable parts that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be during which the main character gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set shoots down because of a few unnecessary bugs that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible fancy on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure in which the main character Jack has character problems and to resolve them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 courses.
As a result, each race is done on a different route and the stages are planned in different environments that differ quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are pretty beautiful even though the technical level is the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowed mountains is very pleasant visually.
The trials are in addition occasionally decorated with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition, the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
Sometimes you struggle to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race), then you run against the clock (classic duel with the timepiece) and then yet another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The main feature is passages outside of the vehicle.
It’s rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is this because this element does not risk bothering and places, in the context described above, in the elements that adorn the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of the previous games.
That means that at the moment there is nothing extraordinary, but it cannot be said to be negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to go see elsewhere.
But while one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of race design.
So everything is OK.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, that of the collisions is not yet in point.
We do not expect from this game complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, in a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it is not entirely good.
During tight surpasses you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self goes into crazy voltages.
Or they find themselves in trouble.
With the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken your figure or you have gone out into the setting the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
Once you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it’s more a tool, in case something isn’t going well, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and you need to find the solution by remembering the route in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same things happen in the same place.
For example, there are certain turns that must be passed in some way otherwise it doesn’t happen.
Otherwise you encounter in a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration whether you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds ahead or a minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and conturb them or brake.
It doesn't matter if you go in front of him because it's "calculated"so that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
During the whole time of the game, you get to certain places, again without worrying about the weather, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This is most annoying at the end of the game when you drive on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must go ahead of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides you the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a lot of times.
One can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a pity because through a simple driving pattern the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it does not matter if it is because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during races.
You should be careful of gasoline pumps on the routes as you can change car there but most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large U.S. cylinders for straight highways, and super sports cars with exotic performances on highly technical routes, for example on rough roads in mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main scheme of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest driver level, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function that, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the hardest hits to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car into the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator indicates between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway wheel that sends you the car directly to the wheel.
At the editorial board we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really think of us as idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What annoys is that in more extreme situations, the image does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This especially applies to accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid image is no longer useful.
The sound is good and the track is good.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack was created in the style of "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confusing.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game does not seem to be over.
Fun is really good but be prepared for mistakes tapping you in the eye with the strength of an airfield reflector.
Students of Velours in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time celebrations that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival are performed 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The theme of the festival consists of two concerts held on November 17.
“Charles University plays an important part in this festival.”
“Among the choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Vaclav Hampl,” says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The culmination of the festival is the concert of the Choir des lycées et classes secondaires which takes place with free entrance on 17 November from 14:00 on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velours" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of higher schools and the Charles University perform.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Smells in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is put under the auspices of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program offers in addition to high-level concerts, msical meetings, a student happening and other activities.
Interested participants will find all the information on the festival’s website www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
The Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a tough war.”
"It will take 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role," this is how Milena Vicenova began her exhibition at the Faculty of Law the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the different EU bodies and their relationships in such a understandable and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from the Charles University Law Faculty could envy her, she showed how she takes her motto "understood and open about Europe" very seriously.
Ms Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
“From the beginning, criticisms resonated that he’s dull, that he’s a rookie, that he can’t fulfill any mission and I have to say that he cut off everyone’s breath because he holds his role to perfection.”
"He is a man who can listen to the 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to be taken by Europe."
She explained the new position of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of a response to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "Which phone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards uniqueness and greater legibility of the EU policy towards states, such as China or India.
No one wants to forbid us our syrecky (cockroaches that smell very strong)
Ms. Vicenova also stated the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs solved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis, or organized a summit for an Eastern Partnership.
She called the fall of the government very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
According to Ms. Ambassador’s words, “activity has reached its full” not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to resolve itself now.
In addition, the new seven-hour budget of the Union must be approved, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
As it would seem that the budget will be thin and in terms of savings, which branch will have the priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the framework of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For a comprehensible Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted corns, differently large bananas, or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.”
She wants to better use the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
In addition, it is regrettable to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, she said, results from several factors, such as the timidity of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and a weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she subsequently highlighted the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
“Believe me, when the Polish, the Hungarian, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me, ‘Hey, what are you doing there, what is this group of Visegrad doing?’ and he is not at all happy.”
According to Ms. Vicenova, in the near future it is new tough fiscal policy rules that await member countries.
This is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not a multi-speed Europe, which prevails rather than a “new European Federation”.
“We have countries in the eurozone and others outside the eurozone.”
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the institute of enhanced cooperation."
First, it was said that countries that want to cooperate with each other and those that don’t want to remain in their corner.”
"There will be a lot of institutions of this type and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," Vicenova expects.
From this perspective, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all issues affecting the EU should be discussed among all EU members and not just the eurozone members.
History of a Brand:
IBM begins the second century of its existence
If someone had to look for the word that most closely expresses IBM’s strategy, the closest one would be “long-term”.
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has passed a hundred years.
The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the company’s first CEO, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a lot of global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENS!" became the footprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the foundation of Watson’s care business culture.
For us, IBM means long-term thinking of continuous movements towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it remained faithful to its core values and yet was not afraid to change everyone else around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will even more"declared for the birthday the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began taking care of his employees as Bata in the Czech Republic – IBM people were the only among the first American employees to have paid vacations, an employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-designed system of rewards for inventors and commercials.
Similarly, IBM has a well-designed customer relationship system.
The company was at the beginning brilliant in the discovery of talents- as one of the first firms to abolish all forms of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is entirely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman – Virginia Rometty – who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for thirty years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has done what is called the jamy, the online brain- storming from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
It is not surprising that he has a lot of ideas - in the company there are almost 500,000 people working.
A company with a good name
