The Mexican Institute of Social Security (IMSS) has announced that it is conducting an investigation to uncover the obesity gene in the case of children and young people, called the Protocol 'Genetic Obesity of Children and Adolescents' which will allow to have the markers associated with overweight.
In a statement, the head of the Medical Research Unit in Biochemistry of the Hospital of Specialties of the 20th Century National Medical Center, Miguel Cruz López, explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social worker had been formed.
This team is supported by specialists and postgraduate students from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Center for Research and Advanced Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
